description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Theatre Staff &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;University Hospitals Dorset NHS Foundation Trust&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For this post you will be based at Poole Hospital &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 5 Vacancies: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Operating Department Practitioners or Registered Nurses &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Recovery Practitioners&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are working closely to develop an expanded service for the Dorset community and wider areas with a view to cross site working. Poole is a great place to live and work where patient care and staff welfare are our top priorities. We are located in Poole town centre near the coast and New Forest. All this is on offer to any nursing and theatre practitioners making their next career move.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;At this exciting time, are you what we are looking for?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;With the management team in place and focus on quality, transformation and service development, we are increasing our operating theatre suite and are looking for motivated people, to join our expanding theatre department across sites delivering a 24 hour service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We offer great opportunities with an extensive educational program, to include the development of Surgical First Assistants (SFA), Anaesthetic Practitioners, Airway management, Assistant Theatre practitioners, nurse associates, leadership and management development to name but a few.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We pride ourselves on our friendly working environment and our desire to lead on Best Practice in the Operating Theatre setting. If you have the knowledge, skills, experience and drive that we are looking for to join our friendly and supportive team, then Poole Hospital theatres is the place for you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working with multi professional colleagues, you will have experience in working in a theatre setting, with a keen interest and skills in recovery. we offer a range of specialities - Obstetric, head and neck, gynaecology, general and colorectal , trauma and orthopaedics and anaesthetics and you will become a valued member of a core team. We encourage duel or multi skilled practitioners, however full training will be given to facilitate development. Your peers, Anaesthetists, surgeons and senior staff will support you to learn new skills and to expand your practice&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be either a:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Registered Operating Department Practitioner or Registered Nurse&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note: if this job requires you to have a DBS check to enable you to properly fulfil the requirements of the job, on appointment you will be required to repay the cost of obtaining a DBS check and this amount will be reclaimed from your salary.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 08/11/2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Provisional interview date: week commencing 16/11/2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Kath Bradley, Clinical Team Manager Recovery&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;kathleen.bradley@uhd.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;0300 019 2971&lt;/p&gt;
